11:40.618 --> 11:42.536
Well, my teacher wants imagery.

11:42.620 --> 11:44.955
Not words like "hot" and "cold."

11:45.039 --> 11:46.039
Uh-huh.

11:47.833 --> 11:49.126
I'll change it.

11:50.419 --> 11:51.420
Ah.

11:51.921 --> 11:55.591
So is this the party line around here?
That I'm unhinged?

11:55.674 --> 11:58.094
- That's the book on me?
- Pretty much.

12:00.513 --> 12:01.513
Great.

12:05.601 --> 12:08.062
I don't understand
why the attorney can't handle this.

12:08.145 --> 12:09.188
Because they can't.

12:09.271 --> 12:12.650
All right? He had to pluck a zillion strings
to get this through on a Saturday

12:12.733 --> 12:13.818
with nobody else around.

12:18.781 --> 12:22.493
It's not like a scarlet letter.
People file for bankruptcy all the time.

12:22.576 --> 12:24.120
Some even go on to become president.

12:24.203 --> 12:27.123
Let's just keep this thing moving along.
I've got a party to throw.

12:27.206 --> 12:32.378
Absolutely no mention of that whatsoever
to the trustee. All right? Am I clear?

12:33.712 --> 12:36.090
So this represents your
assets in their entirety?

12:36.173 --> 12:38.050
- Yes, sir.
- Condo in Aspen.

12:38.134 --> 12:41.262
Four-bedroom vacation home
in Palm Beach,

12:41.345 --> 12:44.306
including a 58-foot Red Sea Yacht.

12:44.390 --> 12:45.391
The <i>Amabella.</i>

12:45.474 --> 12:47.518
